<paragraph blockId="0.[1249,2136,623,1253]" pageId="0" pageNumber="716">• Small to medium-sized bats, with stout bodies, short to moderately long rostra, no elaborate nose appendages (except in a few genera), small to big ears, complete uropatagiumstretching to ends or just before ends of long tails, and generally long narrow wings.</paragraph>
